<br>
I don't spend much time in DL.  But there is a druid port there, so I'm often porting in.<br>
<br>
Port to DL, on the way to Firiona Vie for some reason.<br>
<br>
Check bat wing supply (notice how I don't check <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> before</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I port.  Good to go there.  Cast Levitate.<br>
<br>
Cast SoW (don't you hate when it drops and you are running from some mob).<br>
<br>
Cast Camouflage.<br>
<br>
As soon as I get going, the snow starts to fall.  By the time I'm on the other side of the tunnel, it is a complete whiteout.  OK, I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> think</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I know how to go.  Just head straight out and when I get to KC, just line up with the pillars on the back side.<br>
<br>
[For those who don't know me, I'm a pretty thin Halfling, I guess.  I tend to run higher than most.]<br>
<br>
Run for a bit.  Look around -- nothing.  Run some more, look some more.  At the time, I'm low enough level that most mobs would eat me for lunch, so I don't want to run on the ground.  Run some more, look some more.  OK, nothing.  I guess I'll have to drift down and get my bearings.  Drifting down.  Cool.  I see the KC walls, but they look sort of strange.  And they are on all sides of me.  &lt;sigh&gt;After falling <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> into</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Karnor's and realizing there is no way out, I port back to the druid ring and start again.<br>
