<br>
Usually, whenever I get lost, I just throw up my hands and make Shjekai run me around cause I can never figure out where the heck I am. Sometimes he can't either. I don't even want to think of how many times he's said, "Babe, how did you manage to DO that?"<br>
<br>
Once, my friend and I were driving home from college, basically from Philly to RI. We normally bypass NYC cause the traffic is evil and cross the river further north. So we get directions from her Russian prof for a "faster " way to go. And they are IN Russian. So she has to translate them for us. Well, she's practically fluent, so ok, no big deal, we fly through New Jersey with no problems. I guess she missed something in the translation cause all of a sudden I see Dodger Stadium on my right. So it starts to sink in that we are a wee bit lost when we drive past a sign that says "Welcome to the Bronx"! We proceed to drive through what feels like every ghetto area in New York for the next hour and a half before we find our way out. The whole time we were totally wigging out-- 2 lost young women in a nice car-- yup, we were asking to die. That was also the trip where we got lost in central CT. A 5 hour drive that became a 12 hour drive. Our mothers were commiserating over the phone and were minutes away from calling the state police and having them search for us, lol.<br>
<br>
The moral of this story: Directions in a language that is NOT your native tongue is a very very stupid idea. Yes I should have known this ahead of time :p <p><center><b>Miyyu Kamatari</b></center>
